Update Makefile  Fixed build detection to properly distinguish between Android/Termux and regular Linux environments. Android systems report as "Linux" in kernel checks but require different compiler flags and libraries.  The fix ensures:  · Android builds get Termux-compatible flags (-D__ANDROID__, iconv linking) · Regular Linux builds get standard flags (-DWITH_HWMON) · Proper library linking for each platform · No flag conflicts between environments  Detection order is critical since both systems identify as Linux at kernel level.
